<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="440" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1465,1958]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1465,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Description.</emphasis>
General appearance as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Fang &amp; Xing, 2018" authorityName="Fang &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2018" box="[607,849,1465,1489]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Longicornus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[607,849,1465,1489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Longicornus furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,952,1465,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[860,952,1465,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but body color darker and frontoclypeus with dark, transverse streaks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1465,1958]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis box="[199,373,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side elongate, base wide, apex narrow, with numerous macrosetae on posterior area (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1573,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,205,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Longicornus biprocessus sp. nov. 34. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 35. Valve, ventral view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus, ventral view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Connective, dorsal view; 40. Style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441745/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft tapered in lateral view, with two pairs of processes: one pair spiniform and arising from ventral margin near base; other pair long and slender, arising from mediodorsal margin, extended to apex of shaft and directed caudally. Gonopore apical on dorsal side (
<figureCitation box="[790,923,1645,1670]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,205,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Longicornus biprocessus sp. nov. 34. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 35. Valve, ventral view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus, ventral view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Connective, dorsal view; 40. Style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441745/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Figs.37, 38</figureCitation>
). Connective with arms nearly 1/5 length of stem (
<figureCitation box="[219,303,1681,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1312,1334]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,205,1279]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1291]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Longicornus biprocessus sp. nov. 34. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 35. Valve, ventral view; 36. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 37. Aedeagus, ventral view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Connective, dorsal view; 40. Style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441745/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1465,1958]" box="[199,1005,1717,1742]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
