<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="440" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1465,1958]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1825,1850]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[662,843,1825,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Longicornus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipuncatus">
<emphasis box="[662,843,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">L. flavipuncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the long aedeagal shaft with two pairs of processes medially on the dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="440" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1465,1958]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1897,1922]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is derived from the Latin words “ 
<emphasis box="[1014,1035,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">bi</emphasis>
-”and “ 
<emphasis box="[1121,1230,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">processus</emphasis>
”, referring to the aedeagus with two pairs of processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
